LanguageData.HaulersDream.Alert.CannotUnloadDesc.NoSt:
These pawns are carrying collected items with nowhere to put them — no stockpile or dumping zone on the map accepts them, and no reachable spot was found. Add a stockpile (a Dumping Stockpile accepts rock chunks and most refuse), or allow their item type on an existing one:

{0}

Until then the items stay in their inventory. Click this alert to cycle to the pawns; hover to point them out.

LanguageData.HaulersDream.Alert.CannotUnloadDesc.Stuc:
These pawns have been carrying collected items for a long time without unloading them. Storage may be unreachable from where they are, or another mod may be repeatedly cancelling their hauling/unloading job:

{0}

Check for a reachable, allowed stockpile, and for a mod interrupting their jobs. Click this alert to cycle to the pawns; hover to point them out.
